# Local dev and production both default to /api (same-origin cookies).
# Local: Vite proxies /api to the API (default http://localhost:3000).
# Production: Cloudflare Pages rewrites /api to Cloud Run (see public/_redirects).
#
# To test locally against a deployed API while keeping same-origin cookies:
# VITE_DEV_API_PROXY_TARGET="https://split-the-bill-api-1099488675893.northamerica-northeast2.run.app"
# Also set COOKIE_SECURE=false on the Cloud Run API while testing over http://localhost.
#
# Only set VITE_API_URL if you intentionally bypass the /api proxy. Then the API must use
# COOKIE_SAME_SITE=none and COOKIE_SECURE=true, with WEB_ORIGIN matching your frontend origin.
